{% elif predicate == "enable" %}
{% if target.name == "index-object" and libraryContext.isLibraryWide %}
Purpose:
  Build or rebuild this library's aggregate search index.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} enable [--jsonl]

Notes:
  - This is a full rebuild from registered present archives.
  - Missing or unreadable library archive members are skipped and reported.
  - Progress is emitted as text by default, or line-delimited events with `--jsonl`.
  - `--json` is not supported for enable because progress is streamed.
  - Library indexes are local derived state under Wiki Graph staging, not files inside the library folder.
  - Rebuild holds the library write lock; concurrent `scan`, `add`, `rebind`, `disable`, archive `move`, or archive `remove` commands for the same library cannot run at the same time.
  - Archive writes can mark the aggregate index dirty; rebuild again before relying on library-wide query when status reports dirty or stale.
{% else %}
Purpose:
  Enable searchable FTS index support for this archive on this machine.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} enable [--jsonl]

Notes:
  - This initializes or repairs the local searchable index and may take time on large archives.
  - After the index is enabled, CLI archive writes keep it synchronized automatically.
  - Do not run this after every generation job; run it when `inspect` says query support is unavailable or the index needs repair.
  - By default the index is stored as local cache outside the `.wikg` archive. Use `embed` when the index should travel with the archive.
  - Enabling uses local CPU and disk only; it does not call an LLM provider.
  - Text success output is a short status summary.
  - With `--jsonl`, progress is emitted as line-delimited event records such as step/status/error records.
  - After enable succeeds, `--query`, `related --query`, and `evidence --query` become available.
{% endif %}
{% elif predicate == "disable" %}
{% if target.name == "index-object" and libraryContext.isLibraryWide %}
Purpose:
  Disable this library index and remove its current local materialization.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} disable [--json]

Notes:
  - This does not delete the library registry, metadata, folder, or managed `.wikg` archives.
  - Library-wide `--query` and naked scope enumeration will fail until the index is enabled again.
  - Library indexes do not support archive-style `embed` or `external` modes.
  - Disable holds the library write lock and cannot run concurrently with membership changes or index rebuild for the same library.
{% else %}
Purpose:
  Disable searchable FTS index support for this archive and remove the current index materialization.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} disable [--json]

Notes:
  - Disabling removes the current local or embedded index materialization.
  - After disable succeeds, `--query`, `related --query`, and `evidence --query` are unavailable until `enable` or `embed` is run again.
  - Use this when intentionally dropping index state, not as routine cleanup after generation.
{% endif %}
{% elif predicate == "embed" %}
{% if target.name == "index-object" and libraryContext.isLibraryWide %}
Purpose:
  This library index does not support embedded archive index storage.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} enable --help

Notes:
  - Library indexes are local derived state under Wiki Graph staging.
  - Use `enable` to build the library index or `disable` to remove it.
{% else %}
Purpose:
  Use an archive-embedded searchable FTS index.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} embed [--json]

Notes:
  - This switches the index storage policy to the `.wikg` archive and ensures the embedded index is current.
  - After embedding, CLI archive writes keep the embedded index synchronized automatically.
  - This makes the archive more portable, but increases archive size.
  - Use it when distributing a `.wikg` with keyword retrieval ready for another machine.
{% endif %}
{% elif predicate == "external" %}
{% if target.name == "index-object" and libraryContext.isLibraryWide %}
Purpose:
  This library index does not support archive externalization.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} enable --help

Notes:
  - Library indexes are already local derived state under Wiki Graph staging.
  - Use `enable` to build the library index or `disable` to remove it.
{% else %}
Purpose:
  Use external local-cache storage for the searchable FTS index.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} external [--json]

Notes:
  - This switches the index storage policy back to local cache outside the `.wikg` archive.
  - The archive no longer carries embedded index data.
  - Externalizing does not guarantee a current local materialization on this machine.
  - Run `{{ commandName }} {{ uri }} enable` to build or repair local query support after switching to external storage.
{% endif %}
{% elif predicate == "clean" %}
Purpose:
  Remove completed local generation jobs.

Usage:
  {{ commandName }} {{ uri }} clean

Notes:
  - Removes succeeded, failed, and canceled jobs whose status has not changed for at least seven days.
  - Deletes those job records plus their workspace, cache, log, and event files.
  - Does not remove waiting, running, paused, or recently finished jobs.
  - Does not stop workers or cancel active jobs.
  - Does not support `--json`, `--jsonl`, `--dry-run`, or `--confirm`; output is a short text count.
  - Use `{{ commandName }} gc --help` for broader runtime cleanup and dry-run support.
